    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187981>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Chlamydopleon aculeatum Ortmann, 1893, lectotype (A – D, F – H) and paralectotype (E): A, anterior body region of male; B, lobes at postero-dorsal margin of carapace; C, penis, lateral view on inner face; D, third pleopod of the subterminal male, lateral view on inner face; E, endopod of uropod, lateral; F, endopod of uropod, ventral; G, terminal portion of pleon, dorsal; H, detail of (G) showing tip of telson. — Subterminal males in Chlamydopleon dissimile (Coifmann, 1937), lectotype from Brazil (J, K) and specimen with total length of 7.7 mm from Georgia (L): J, lobes at postero-dorsal margin of carapace; K, terminal portion of exopod of third pleopod, lateral; L, outer branch of exopod of third pleopod. Abbreviations: b, blade; is, inner stylet; ob, outer branch; vp, ventral process." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187981/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

